result.name: Golden Monkey

reviews.text: Soup base was really tasty and not greasy at all. It is oddly a bit on the sweet and tangy side for a beef soup base but it's definitely refreshing. Good portions and prices are decent for this area, since it costs $60 just to get mediocre lunch at the open-air market place or $80 for a nice bowl of noodles in a nicely renovated, air conditioned and clean restaurant. The place is usually busy but still has some seats available because a lot of people order take out. I would definitely come back here again.

Revisited for lunch after 2 years as passing by after work. Lunch was not as good as 2 years ago anymore. Staff attitude was poor. We were in group of 6 and would like a more spacious table as we have bags and laptops. Staff forced us to switch from table to table and we were asked to sit with other customers. Apparently we were here beyond lunch peak period where it had only 2 to 3 customers. We will not come again next time and would rather go further place for lunch

The prices are reasonable and it is a place that I enjoy going to after school given the very open atmosphere. The staff are very understanding and helpful! If you need to get a bite around the area, I would recommend here

Food is very good, but they use SO MUCH PLASTIC!  DRINK IS IN PLASTIC CUP, WITH A PLASTIC SPOON AND A PLASTIC STRAW, all of which is thrown away.  Mentioned to the staff to use less, but they say the boss wants it like that and laughed.  Very disappointing to see they care so little about something so easily improved.  Maybe the boss doesn't like the planet but the rest of us do.  Please change this!
i loved the teas but i think they should have more soup in their noodles
